          "data": {
            "list": [
              {
                "artifactPos": "",
                "desc": "<p>One who wished to improve the range and accuracy of slingshots discovered that<br>Power increases range, but costs accuracy.<br>So slingshot rocks were replaced with long wooden poles that sported feathers for stability.<br>The slingshot's limbs were lengthened and the ends recurved to increase pull.<br>It then dawned on him that he had made a bow.</p>",
